        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 9:41PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 941 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Hays, or 12 miles north of Zortman, moving north
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lodge Pole.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
